    {
      "id": 4,
      "description": "That June, experts from the biological control joint service, the SMCB, were sent on a mission to evaluate the impact of the contamination on the inhabitants of Tureia. They precisely identified the number of rainwater cisterns and their location on the atoll, and measured the levels of fission products in the water, as revealed in this document, which is now declassified.![](https://fp-nuclear-bucket.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com/IMAGE/ENC/ENC-2-map.jpg)_Map of rainwater catchment cisterns in village Fakamaru, Tureia, 1971. Declassiefied document: 05-1971 - 02-12-58._ ",
